{"title":"Potion of enlightenment","url":"https://nethackwiki.com/wiki/Potion_of_enlightenment","type":"markdown","data":"**[English]()** • [中文（中国大陆）‎](/wiki/Potion_of_enlightenment/zh-CN \"Potion of enlightenment/zh-CN\")\n\n| ! [![Pink potion.png](/images/7/79/Pink_potion.png)](/wiki/File:Pink_potion.png) |                                                               |\n| -------------------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------- |\n| Name                                                                             | enlightenment                                                 |\n| Appearance                                                                       | [random](/wiki/Randomised_appearance \"Randomised appearance\") |\n| Base price                                                                       | 200 [zm](/wiki/Zorkmid \"Zorkmid\")                             |\n| Weight                                                                           | 20                                                            |\n| Monster use                                                                      | *Will not be used by monsters.*                               |\n\nA **potion of enlightenment** is a type of [potion](/wiki/Potion \"Potion\") that appears in *[NetHack](/wiki/NetHack \"NetHack\")*.\n\n[ ]\n\n## Contents\n\n- [1 Generation](#Generation)\n\n- [2 Description](#Description)\n  - [2.1 Alchemy](#Alchemy)\n\n- [3 Strategy](#Strategy)\n\n- [4 History](#History)\n\n- [5 Messages](#Messages)\n\n- [6 Variants](#Variants)\n\n  - [6.1 UnNetHack](#UnNetHack)\n  - [6.2 Hack'EM](#Hack.27EM)\n\n- [7 References](#References)\n\n## Generation\n\nThe potion of enlightenment makes up 2% of randomly-generated potions.\n\n## Description\n\n- *Main article: [Enlightenment](/wiki/Enlightenment \"Enlightenment\")*\n\n[Quaffing](/wiki/Quaff \"Quaff\") a non-cursed [exercises](/wiki/Exercise \"Exercise\") [wisdom](/wiki/Wisdom \"Wisdom\") and provides [enlightenment](/wiki/Enlightenment \"Enlightenment\"), allowing you to momentarily see your character's [intrinsics](/wiki/Intrinsic \"Intrinsic\") and other attributes.[\\[1\\]](#cite_note-1) A blessed potion additionally increases [intelligence](/wiki/Intelligence \"Intelligence\") and wisdom by 1.[\\[2\\]](#cite_note-2)\n\nQuaffing a cursed potion abuses wisdom and prints a message with no other effect, prompting you to type-[name](/wiki/Name \"Name\") the potion.[\\[3\\]](#cite_note-3)\n\n### Alchemy\n\n[Dipping](/wiki/Dipping \"Dipping\") to mix together a [potion of confusion](/wiki/Potion_of_confusion \"Potion of confusion\") and either a [potion of gain level](/wiki/Potion_of_gain_level \"Potion of gain level\") or a [potion of gain energy](/wiki/Potion_of_gain_energy \"Potion of gain energy\") has a 3⁄10 chance of producing potions of enlightenment.\n\nMixing a [potion of levitation](/wiki/Potion_of_levitation \"Potion of levitation\") with a potion of enlightenment has a 3⁄5 chance of producing a [potion of gain level](/wiki/Potion_of_gain_level \"Potion of gain level\").\n\n## Strategy\n\nPotions of enlightenment are sometimes worth blessing to increase your mental stats. Otherwise, they are frequently saved for [alchemy](/wiki/Alchemy \"Alchemy\") once identified to use in creating potions of gain level.\n\n## History\n\nThe potion of enlightenment first appears in [NetHack 3.0.0](/wiki/NetHack_3.0.0 \"NetHack 3.0.0\").\n\n## Messages\n\n- You have an uneasy feeling...\n\n  You quaffed a cursed potion of enlightenment.\n\n## Variants\n\n### UnNetHack\n\nIn [UnNetHack](/wiki/UnNetHack \"UnNetHack\"), there is a 3⁄5 chance of a potion of enlightenment generating in the [boulder](/wiki/Boulder \"Boulder\")-blocked stash on the last floor of the [Dragon Caves](/wiki/Dragon_Caves \"Dragon Caves\") at level creation.\n\n### Hack'EM\n\nIn [Hack'EM](/wiki/Hack%27EM \"Hack'EM\"), the last floor of [The Wyrm Caves](/wiki/The_Wyrm_Caves \"The Wyrm Caves\") uses the last floor map from the Dragon Caves of UnNetHack, including the 3⁄5 chance of generating a potion of enlightenment in the stash.\n\n## References\n\n1. [↑](#cite_ref-1) [src/potion.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 713](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/potion.c#L713)\n2. [↑](#cite_ref-2) [src/potion.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 719](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/potion.c#L719)\n3. [↑](#cite_ref-3) [src/potion.c in NetHack 3.6.7, line 716](https://github.com/NetHack/NetHack/blob/NetHack-3.6.7_Released/src/potion.c#L716)\n\n[![This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.7. Click here for more information.](/images/f/f7/Nh367-icon.png)](/wiki/NetHackWiki:Next_version \"This article has been updated to reflect NetHack 3.6.7. Click here for more information.\")\n","html":"<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html class=\"client-nojs\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<title>Potion of enlightenment - NetHack Wiki</title>\n<script>document.documentElement.className = document.documentElement.className.replace( /(^|\\s)client-nojs(\\s|$)/, \"$1client-js$2\" );</script>\n<script>(window.RLQ=window.RLQ||[]).push(function(){mw.config.set({\"wgCanonicalNamespace\":\"\",\"wgCanonicalSpecialPageName\":false,\"wgNamespaceNumber\":0,\"wgPageName\":\"Potion_of_enlightenment\",\"wgTitle\":\"Potion of enlightenment\",\"wgCurRevisionId\":177023,\"wgRevisionId\":177023,\"wgArticleId\":1998,\"wgIsArticle\":true,\"wgIsRedirect\":false,\"wgAction\":\"view\",\"wgUserName\":null,\"wgUserGroups\":[\"*\"],\"wgCategories\":[\"Nethack-367 articles\",\"Potions\"],\"wgBreakFrames\":false,\"wgPageContentLanguage\":\"en\",\"wgPageContentModel\":\"wikitext\",\"wgSeparatorTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDigitTransformTable\":[\"\",\"\"],\"wgDefaultDateFormat\":\"dmy\",\"wgMonthNames\":[\"\",\"January\",\"February\",\"March\",\"April\",\"May\",\"June\",\"