"100.00%   30.184      1 -total\",\" 24.61%    7.428      3 Template:Refsrc\",\" 24.51%    7.397      1 Template:Languages\",\" 17.79%    5.368      5 Template:Languages/Lang\",\" 16.11%    4.863      1 Template:Nethack-367\",\" 12.38%    3.736      1 Template:Version_icon\",\" 10.98%    3.314      3 Template:Refsrc/link\",\"  8.60%    2.597      1 Template:Potion\",\"  8.16%    2.464      1 Template:Message\",\"  8.04%    2.428      1 Template:Top_icon\"]},\"cachereport\":{\"timestamp\":\"20240926185732\",\"ttl\":604800,\"transientcontent\":false}}});mw.config.set({\"wgBackendResponseTime\":79});});</script>\n\t</body>\n</html>\n","rawPage":"{{languages}}\n{{potion\n |name=enlightenment\n |cost=200\n}}\n\nA '''potion of enlightenment''' is a type of [[potion]] that appears in ''[[NetHack]]''.\n\n==Generation==\nThe potion of enlightenment makes up 2% of randomly-generated potions.\n\n==Description==\n{{main|Enlightenment}}\n[[Quaff]]ing a non-cursed [[exercise]]s [[wisdom]] and provides [[enlightenment]], allowing you to momentarily see your character's [[intrinsic]]s and other attributes.{{refsrc|src/potion.c|713|nethack=3.6.7}} A blessed potion additionally increases [[intelligence]] and wisdom by 1.{{refsrc|src/potion.c|719|nethack=3.6.7}}\n\nQuaffing a cursed potion abuses wisdom and prints a message with no other effect, prompting you to type-[[name]] the potion.{{refsrc|src/potion.c|716|nethack=3.6.7}}\n\n===Alchemy===\n[[Dipping]] to mix together a [[potion of confusion]] and either a [[potion of gain level]] or a [[potion of gain energy]] has a {{frac|3|10}} chance of producing potions of enlightenment.\n\nMixing a [[potion of levitation]] with a potion of enlightenment has a {{frac|3|5}} chance of producing a [[potion of gain level]].\n\n==Strategy==\nPotions of enlightenment are sometimes worth blessing to increase your mental stats. Otherwise, they are frequently saved for [[alchemy]] once identified to use in creating potions of gain level.\n\n==History==\nThe potion of enlightenment first appears in [[NetHack 3.0.0]].\n\n==Messages==\n{{message|You have an uneasy feeling...|You quaffed a cursed potion of enlightenment.}}\n\n==Variants==\n===UnNetHack===\nIn [[UnNetHack]], there is a {{frac|3|5}} chance of a potion of enlightenment generating in the [[boulder]]-blocked stash on the last floor of the [[Dragon Caves]] at level creation.\n\n===Hack'EM===\nIn [[Hack'EM]], the last floor of [[The Wyrm Caves]] uses the last floor map from the Dragon Caves of UnNetHack, including the {{frac|3|5}} chance of generating a potion of enlightenment in the stash.\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n{{nethack-367}}\n[[Category:Potions|Enlightenment]]"}